ers/nyurik/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nyurik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nyurik/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nyurik/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nyurik/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nyurik/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nyurik/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2022-02-14T22:07:26Z", "updated_at": "2023-05-01T05:56:45Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The custom message in [assert_eq!(...)](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/macro.assert_eq.html) macro is shown right after the `right:`. This is hard to read because the value strings could be very long.  I think it is better to print the custom message (if available) on a separate line. \n\n```rust\nfn main() {\n    let a = 10;\n    let b = 20;\n    assert_eq!(a, b, \"Values {a} and {b}\");\n}\n```\n\nThe above [code](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=d534f77fd85202724f3bd08453294573) (playground) prints this:\n\n```none\nthread 'main' panicked at 'assertion failed: `(left == right)`\n  left: `10`,\n right: `20`: Values 10 and 20', src/main.rs:4:5\n```\n\n### Suggested output\n```none\nthread 'main' panicked at 'assertion failed: `(left == right)`\n   left: `10`,\n  right: `20`,\ncontext: Values 10 and 20', src/main.rs:4:5\n```\n\nNote that custom message and the location in source are still on the same line\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"nyurik\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/94005/reactions", "total_count": 6, "+1": 6, "